<div class="row">
    <div class="column4 item">
        <div class="section shadow white rc">
            <div class="item-title"><span class="font-blue icon-upload-cloud"></span><span class="item-title-text">Upload</span></div>
            <div class="item-text">Upload your favorite books in <strong class="djvu">djvu</strong> or <strong class="pdf">pdf</strong></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="column4 item">
        <div class="section shadow white rc">
            <div class="item-title"><span class="font-yellow icon-laptop"></span><span class="item-title-text">Access</span></div>
            <div class="item-text">Read your books on any device with web-browser</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="column4 item">
        <div class="section shadow white rc">
            <div class="item-title"><span class="font-green icon-book-open"></span><span class="item-title-text">Read</span></div>
            <div class="item-text">Our service remembers the page where you stopped reading</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="section shadow try white rc">
    <% if signed_in? %>
    Please <%= link_to( "<span class='genericon genericon-cloud-upload'></span>Upload".html_safe, new_book_path, :class => 'btn big blue rc' ) %> and <%= link_to( "<span class='genericon genericon-book'></span>Read".html_safe, books_path, :class => 'btn green big rc' ) %> Your books
    <% elsif is_guest? %>
    Guest, to access all features, <%= link_to( "<span class='genericon genericon-facebook-alt'></span>Sign in with facebook".html_safe, user_omniauth_authorize_path(:facebook), :class => 'btn dark-blue big rc' ) %> or <%= link_to( "<span class='genericon genericon-key'></span>Sign up".html_safe, new_user_registration_path, :class => 'btn yellow big rc' ) %>
    <% else %>
    <%= link_to( "<span class='genericon genericon-reply'></span>Try It Now!".html_safe, try_as_guest_books_path, :class => 'btn big red rc' ) %>
    or
    <%= link_to( "<span class='genericon genericon-key'></span>Sign up".html_safe, new_user_registration_path, :class => 'btn big yellow rc' ) %>
    and get access to all features
    <% end %>
</div>
<div class="section shadow white rc">
<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
  DPReader allows you to store and read books in PDF and DJVU formats from different devices.
  You donâ€™t need to remember the page where you stopped reading because this is done by DPReader.
</p>
<p>
  For example, you can start reading the book on your tablet, and continue on your laptop.
</p>
<p>
    Application was created with the use of <%= link_to "Ruby on Rails", "http://rubyonrails.org/" %>,
    <%= link_to "pdf.js", "http://mozilla.github.io/pdf.js/" %>,
    <%= link_to "Postgres", "http://www.postgresql.org/" %> and other nice Open Source Software!
</p>
</div>
<div class="section shadow white rc">
    <h2>Plans for the Future</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Integration with <span class="icon-dropbox font-blue"></span>Dropbox, Google Drive, Yandex Disk,</li>
        <li>working with large PDF and DJVU files,</li>
        <li>release a DPReader app for <span class="icon-android font-green"></span>Android and <span class="icon-appstore font-grey"></span>iOS.</li>
    </ul>
</div>